00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:04,640
No!

485
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,320
So you really knew I was
with them the whole time?

486
00:19:11,399 --> 00:19:12,960
Or was that just another lie?

487
00:19:13,039 --> 00:19:14,360
Another lie?

488
00:19:14,439 --> 00:19:17,080
The only thing we've ever lied
to you about is the dog.

489
00:19:17,159 --> 00:19:18,959
Truth is, he went to a farm.

490
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:21,240
No, I know you stole me
from them.

491
00:19:21,320 --> 00:19:22,440
Stole you?

492
00:19:22,519 --> 00:19:24,200
We didn't steal you.

493
00:19:24,279 --> 00:19:25,480
We took you.

494
00:19:28,240 --> 00:19:29,880
We gotta go.

495
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:31,120
And there's not gonna be
enough room for all the goods
and Daphne.

496
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,679
Oh, okay. Well, as parents,

497
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:35,159
there's only one right
decision to make here.

498
00:19:37,759 --> 00:19:39,040
Damn it! They got away!

499
00:19:41,959 --> 00:19:44,640
Oh, my God,
I feel like such an idiot.

500
00:19:44,719 --> 00:19:45,920
They abandoned me twice.

501
00:19:45,999 --> 00:19:48,080
That's why we never
told you the truth.

502
00:19:48,159 --> 00:19:49,919
We loved you
from the moment we saw you,

503
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,520
and didn't want you
to ever feel

504
00:19:51,599 --> 00:19:54,199
like you were unwanted
for even a second.

505
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:56,200
I love you, too, Moms.

506
00:19:56,279 --> 00:19:59,040
Ooh, angelite.
That cures anxiety.

507
00:20:01,879 --> 00:20:03,359
<i> Velma? Sweetie?</i>

508
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:05,839
<i>-Can you hear me?</i>
-Mom? Is that you?

509
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:07,280
I found you.

510
00:20:07,359 --> 00:20:09,200
But did you, like,
get a weird haircut?

511
00:20:09,279 --> 00:20:10,600
No, Velma, it's me.

512
00:20:10,679 --> 00:20:13,080
The parent who only
abandoned you emotionally.

513
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:15,800
Dad? Wait. Did I die
and go to hell?

514
00:20:15,879 --> 00:20:18,440
Damn it! I always knew
atheism was a gamble.

515
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:19,800
How did you find me?

516
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:22,240
I can locate your phone,
like any good parent.

517
00:20:22,319 --> 00:20:23,640
Okay. Sophie installed it

518
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,119
so you never catch us in bed
talking smack about you.

519
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:28,079
No, no. I don't have
time to sit here

520
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:30,760
and listen to some
too-little-too-late excuse.

521
00:20:30,839 --> 00:20:31,799
Yes, you do.

522
00:20:31,879 --> 00:20:32,920
Because your legs
are still buried.

523
00:20:32,999 --> 00:20:34,440
Now look.

524
00:20:34,519 --> 00:20:36,200
I'm sorry for how much I worked
when you were little,

525
00:20:36,279 --> 00:20:38,239
but I figured you were fine
because you had your mother.

526
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,559
But then she walked out on us,

527
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:40,880
and I wanted
to be there for you,

528
00:20:40,959 --> 00:20:43,200
but it's too hard
because I feel so guilty.

529
00:20:43,279 --> 00:20:45,040
So, I hide at work.

530
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:47,679
But you wouldn't feel guilty
if you just believed
she was kidnapped.

531
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:49,560
Who would kidnap your mother?

532
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:52,280
No one wants to talk about 9/11
that much anymore.

533
00:20:52,359 --> 00:20:55,040
Fine, don't believe me.
I'll just find her on my own.

534
00:20:56,680 --> 00:20:57,719
I'm fine.

535
00:21:01,799 --> 00:21:02,919
Footprints?

536
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,240
People were just here.

537
00:21:04,320 --> 00:21:05,519
And what's this?

538
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:07,640
Jinkies!

539
00:21:07,719 --> 00:21:09,400
"Jinkies"?
Why are you saying "jinkies"?

540
00:21:09,479 --> 00:21:12,079
Is this like when you tried
to make "Keep it frosty"
a thing?

541
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:13,280
No!

542
00:21:13,359 --> 00:21:14,800
Someone wrote "jinkies"
on this paper.

543
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,039
But why?

544
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:17,240
You'll never know, Velma.

545
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:19,720
Oh, no, Dad!
I need you to believe me

546
00:21:19,799 --> 00:21:21,439
that Mom was kidnapped,
or I'm gonna die!

547
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:23,639
Okay, okay, I believe you,
I swear!

548
00:21:23,719 --> 00:21:26,199
-I believe you.
-Oh, my God!

549
00:21:26,280 --> 00:21:27,839
That... That did it.

550
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,759
-She's gone.
-Psych!

551
00:21:29,840 --> 00:21:31,480
Oh, no, she's back. But how?

552
00:21:31,559 --> 00:21:33,599
Hold on. Were you lying
about believing me?

553
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:36,199
Velma, I want
to believe, but...

554
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:37,560
Wait.

555
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,560
Oh, my God, you're right.
She<i> was</i> kidnapped!

556
00:21:39,639 --> 00:21:42,360
I actually believe you,
for real this time.

557
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,680
-He does?
-You do?

558
00:21:43,759 --> 00:21:44,960
He does!

559
00:21:45,039 --> 00:21:46,799
No!

560
00:21:53,119 --> 00:21:55,760
My hallucinations
are finally over.

561
00:21:55,839 --> 00:21:59,040
Are you sure? 'Cause I feel
like you've said that before.

562
00:21:59,119 --> 00:22:00,280
Like a few times.

563
00:22:00,359 --> 00:22:02,880
No, it's over.
I know my dad believes me.

564
00:22:02,959 --> 00:22:04,039
I'm so sorry

565
00:22:04,120 --> 00:22:05,760
-I doubted you, Velma.
-It's okay.

566
00:22:05,839 --> 00:22:08,840
Because when you saw
I was willing to die
for my truth,

567
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:10,359
you finally came around.

568
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:12,599
-Because you do love me.
-Yes.

569
00:22:12,679 --> 00:22:15,960
But also, "jinkies" is written
in your mother's handwriting.

570
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:17,320
She was just here.

571
00:22:17,399 --> 00:22:18,639
Jinkies!

572
00:22:18,719 --> 00:22:21,000
Okay, now you're totally
trying to make it a thing.

573
00:22:32,039 --> 00:22:35,120
So, if this was all about
your dad believing you,

574
00:22:35,199 --> 00:22:38,680
how did making you laugh
also stop your hallucinations?

575
00:22:38,759 --> 00:22:40,439
Right? Or kissing Daphne?

576
00:22:40,519 --> 00:22:41,639
"Kissing Daphne"?

577
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:43,039
Uh, the point is, I don't know,

578
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:44,519
but I'm sure
I'll figure it out.

579
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,760
It would be pretty lazy not to.
Now, come on!

580
00:22:46,839 --> 00:22:49,319
Whoever has my mom,
and removed those
girls' brains,

581
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:51,760
was just here.
So the question is,

582
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:53,080
where'd they go?

